@Bobkit use VLC Media Player, it can play virtually ANY video file with almost any codec. FYI, the reason some movies wont play on some media player is because your computer doesnt have the codec that the movie file was encoded (made) with. using VLC will usually fix that but for some reason if youre still having trouble download and install a codec pack. for Vista something like this; http://www.softpedia.com/get/Multimedia/Video/Codec-Packs-Video-Codecs/Advanced-Vista-Codec-Package.shtml
for XP; www.xpcodecpack.com
